	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-07-17T04:18:58">Ovoca Gold plc is a gold exploration and mine development company. The Company is focused on the exploration of metals and other minerals in Russia. The Company operates through two business segments, which include exploration activities and investment. Its exploration activities are carried out by subsidiary companies, Comtrans, Bulun and Magsel, which are carried out in the Russian Federation. The Company's investing activities are carried out by another subsidiary company, Silver Star Limited, a company located in Bermuda. The Company operates two properties, which include Stakhanovsky and Rassoshinskaya. Its Stakhanovsky property is located approximately 40 kilometers north of Susuman, Magadan Region, and covers an area of 73 square kilometers. Its Rassoshinskaya property is located in the North Eastern part of the Magadan Region about 200 kilometers from the town of Simchan and covers an area of 2,460 square kilometers.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-07-06T13:11:28">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 31 December 2014, Ovoca Gold plc revenues was not reported. Net loss decreased 55% to EUR6.6M. Lower net loss reflects Exploration Activities segment loss decrease of 97% to EUR358K. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items increased from -EUR0.17 to -EUR0.08.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
